# Invariants

## 1. Trains only travel one direction per each track.
## 2. An approach signal will always precede a depart signal.
## 3. An alarm will always sound after an approach event
## 4. While a train is present there shall be an alarm and barrier engaged.
## 5. While a train is approaching, an alarm shall sound and a barrier shall lower after 10 seconds.
## 6. While trains are absent, no barrier will be engaged.
## 7. If multiple trains are present, the barrier will not disengage until the last train departs
